				\begin{document}$$P( \% )=\left(1-{\sum }_{i}^{n}{W}_{{\rm{i}}}\right)\times 100 \% $$\end{document}P(%)=1−∑inWi×100%, in which Wi is the mass fraction of impure elements and n is the number of impure elements.
